  m_text: Carrots are root vegetables known for their crisp texture, sweet flavor,
    and bright orange color, although they can also be found in purple, red, yellow,
    and white varieties. They grow underground as a tapered taproot, while feathery
    green leaves extend above the soil. Carrots are typically cultivated in loose,
    well-drained soil to allow the roots to develop straight and smooth. They are
    rich in nutrients, particularly beta-carotene, which the body converts into vitamin
    A, making them beneficial for vision and overall health. Carrots are versatile
    in cooking and can be eaten raw, roasted, steamed, or used in soups, salads,
    and juices.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
