  m_text: Beetroot, commonly known as beets, is a root vegetable recognized for its
    deep red or purple color, though golden and striped varieties also exist. It
    grows as a rounded taproot beneath the soil, with leafy green tops that are also
    edible and nutritious. Beetroot has a naturally sweet, earthy flavor and a firm
    texture when raw, becoming tender when cooked. It is rich in essential nutrients
    such as folate, iron, fiber, and antioxidants, which contribute to heart health
    and improved blood circulation. Beets can be consumed in a variety of ways, including
    raw in salads, roasted, boiled, or blended into juices, and they are also used
    as a natural food coloring due to their intense pigment.
