  m_text: "Brown mushrooms, often referred to as cremini or baby bella mushrooms,
    are a variety of edible fungi known for their smooth, tan-to-dark brown caps
    and firm texture. They are essentially a more mature version of white button
    mushrooms, offering a deeper, earthier flavor that becomes even richer when cooked.
    These mushrooms grow in dark, moist environments and have a short stem with gills
    underneath the cap, where spores are produced. Brown mushrooms are low in calories
    but provide important nutrients such as B vitamins, selenium, and antioxidants.
    They are highly versatile in cooking and can be saut\xE9ed, roasted, grilled,
    or added to soups, sauces, and stir-fries to enhance flavor and texture."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
